Diagnosis of BE as the primary endpoint will be defined at three different levels of certainty:
Diagnosis by the endoscopist or gastroenterologist following BSG guidelines
∘ > 3 cm likely correct;
∘ < 3 cm more suspect unless biopsy with IM;
Confirmed by study pathologist or gastroenterologist
∘ >C1 or >M3 +IM on biopsy;
IM on biopsy
∘ any length.

Once consent has been obtained:II.
Lifestyle and family history questionnaire, covering education, history of smoking and alcohol, and any family history of heartburn, BE, oesophageal cancer and any other type of cancer.III.
Perceived risk of oesophageal cancer, using 2 items which have been widely used for other cancer risk assessments to assess perceived risk of developing EAC and perceived risk compared with a person of the same age (relative risk) [24];
